column1: organisation_name
column3: What proportion of patient consultations do health and care professionals request digitally from colleagues or other specialties?
column4: What proportion of laboratory tests are requested through a digital order system?
column5: What proportion of radiology tests are requested through a digital order system?
column6: What proportion of requests for any other diagnostic tests are made through a digital order system?
column7: Digital orders are created in a structured format and held as part of the patients' and service users' digital care record.
column8: Digital orders are pre-populated with information held in patient and service users' digital record.
column9: When making diagnostic test requests, health and care professionals have access to department, speciality or organisation level request/order sets.
column10: Health and care professionals are alerted of duplicate test requests.
column11: What proportion of inpatients are positively identified at the point of sample collection and specimen labelling prior to all diagnostic tests being performed?
column12: Requests received by diagnostic services are automatically integrated into digital workflows to enable booking, triaging or scheduling.
column13: Health and care professionals can track the status of requests to diagnostic services through to completion.
column14: What proportion of laboratory test results are available to health and care professionals digitally?
column15: What proportion of radiology test results are available to health and care professionals digitally?
column16: What proportion of results from any other diagnostic tests are available to health and care professionals digitally?
column17: Health and care professionals have digital access to all relevant diagnostic test results and images for patients and service users under their care.
column18: Digital results are held in a structured format to enable clinical decision support and data extraction.
column19: Health and care professionals are automatically alerted of all results that require acknowledgement by them.
column20: Health and care professionals can digitally access diagnostic test results and images quickly and easily at the point of care.
